  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Crack Attack!</refname>
    <refpurpose>multiplayer OpenGL puzzle game like "Tetris Attack"</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage</command>
      <group choice="REQ">
        <group choice="REQ"><arg>--server <replaceable>PORT</replaceable></arg>
	       <arg choice="OPT">-X</arg><arg choice="OPT">--wait</arg>
	</group>
        <group choice="REQ"><arg><replaceable>SERVER</replaceable></arg>
	       <arg choice="OPT">-X</arg>
	</group>
	<group choice="REQ"><arg>--solo</arg><arg choice="OPT">-X</arg></group>
      </group>
      <arg choice="OPT">--name <replaceable>NAME</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>&package is roughly based on the Super Nintendo game
 "Tetris Attack".  Slowly, your stack of colored blocks grows from the
 bottom, and you've got to make sure it never reaches the top.  If it
 does, you lose.  To eliminate blocks from the stack, line up at least
 three of one color, horizontally or vertically.  Once you do, those
 blocks disappear, and put off slightly your inevitable demise.</para>
 
 <para>Crack Attack essentially requires hardware acceleration.  For
 XFree users, this means you want <abbrev>DRI</abbrev>.</para>
  </refsect1>
